name: FedEx Global Education Center
directions: 1st, 2nd, & 3rd floors
comment: Parking at/ near this building is hard before 5pm. You can try parking at the State Employee's Credit Union across Pittsboro St during business hours. Bathrooms have a common outer door and then multi-stall men's or women's. The 3rd floor has shower spaces inside the main door labeled for men and inside the women's door. The shower rooms do not have toilets. Building & bathroom doors have buttons to auto-open doors, and there are accessible elevators.

name: Starbucks
directions: On the left as soon as you walk into the store. There is an alcove with three doors. The two bathroom doors have standard restroom signage with English and braille.
comment: No key or code, two gender-neutral single bathrooms.  The baristas will not hassle you about buying something to use the bathroom.  Regarding handicap accessibility, the bathrooms are spacious enough to maneuver a chair in and have handrails. There are two handicap parking spots right by the entrance.  All the doors are manual swinging doors though.
